Privacy Policy
Effective Date: [28.04.2025]
This Privacy Policy outlines how the Lavanta Ride mobile application (hereinafter referred to as
"App", "we", "our", or "us") collects, uses, and protects your personal data while using our
scooter rental services, in accordance with the applicable Turkish legislation, including the Law
on the Protection of Personal Data No. 6698 (KVKK).
1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:
 Personal Information: Name, phone number, email address, driver’s license details (if
required), and photos (if uploaded).
 Payment Information: Data related to the payment card or system used for scooter
rentals, processed through a secure third-party provider (we do not store your card
details).
 Device Information: Phone model, operating system, IP address, and other technical
specifications.
 Location Data: GPS data to display nearby scooters and track rental trips.
 Usage Data: Ride history, rental duration, routes taken, and user preferences.
2. How We Use Your Information
Your data is used for the following purposes:
 To provide scooter rental services and calculate ride fees.
 To ensure the secure operation of the App and payment processes.
 To show nearby available scooters and optimize ride routes.
 To communicate with you (e.g., booking confirmations, notifications, support).
 To perform analytics and improve our service quality and user experience.
 To fulfill our legal and regulatory obligations under KVKK.
3. Sharing Your Information
We may share your information in the following cases:
 With payment service providers to process your transactions (we do not store your card
data).
 With contractors and technical service partners who help operate the App.
 With public authorities, if required by law or regulation.
 In connection with a business transfer, such as a merger or acquisition.
4. Data Retention and Security
We retain your personal data only for as long as necessary to provide our services and comply
with legal obligations.
We implement technical and organizational security measures, including encryption and access
controls, in compliance with the requirements of the KVKK.
5. Your Rights (under KVKK)
You have the right to:
 Learn whether your personal data is being processed.
 Request information about the processing of your data.
 Request a copy of your personal data.
 Request correction or deletion of inaccurate or unlawfully processed data.
 Withdraw your consent where processing is based on your consent.
To exercise your rights, please contact us at: info@lavantaride.com
6. Policy Updates
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be made available in the
App along with the updated effective date. Continued use of the App after such updates signifies
your acceptance of the new terms.
7. Contact Us
If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact:
Lavanta Ride
Email: info@lavantaride.com
